    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>

<p>Given \(\underline{r} = {@co1@}\underline{i} \; + \; {@co2@}\underline{j}\): </p>

<ol class="HELM_parts">

<li><p>Find \(\underline{\dot{r}} =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] \(\underline{i} \; + \; \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] \(\underline{j}\).&nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>

<li><p>Find  \(\underline{\ddot{r}} =\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] \(\underline{i} \; + \; \) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] \(\underline{j}\).&nbsp;[[feedback:prt2]]</p></li>

<li><p>Find \( |\underline{r}| = \)  [[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p></li>

<li><p>Find \(\underline{r}\cdot\underline{\dot{r}} = \)[[input:ans6]] [[validation:ans6]] [[feedback:prt4]]</p>
<p>From your answer deduce whether the following statement is True or False:</p>
<p> The position vector \(\underline{r}\) and the velocity vector \(\underline{\dot{r}}\) are perpendicular. [[input:ans7]] [[validation:ans7]] [[feedback:prt5]]</p></li>




</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<h4 class="HELM_solution">Solution</h4>
<p>We are given the vector: \(\underline{r} = {@co1@}\underline{i} \; + \; {@co2@}\underline{j}.\)</p>
<p><br></p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">

    <li>
        <p> \( \dfrac{d}{dt}({@co1@}) = {@ta1@} \) and \( \dfrac{d}{dt}({@co2@}) = {@ta2@} \).</p>
        <p>So we have \( \underline{\dot{r}} = \dfrac{d}{dt}( \underline{r}) = {@ta1@}\underline{i} {@ta2@}\underline{j} \).</p>
    </li>

    <li>
        <p> \( \dfrac{d}{dt}({@ta1@}) = {@ta3@} \) and \( \dfrac{d}{dt}({@ta2@}) = {@ta4@} \).</p>
        <p>So we have \( \underline{\ddot{r}} = {@ta3@}\underline{i} {@ta4@}\underline{j} \).</p>
    </li>

    <li>
        <p>Using the trigonometric identity \( \displaystyle\sin^2(x) + \displaystyle\cos^2(x) = 1\) for all \(x\), we have</p>
        <p>\( \sqrt{{@co1@}^2 + {@co2@}^2} = 1\).</p>
    </li>

    <li>
        <p> \( \left( {@co1@}\underline{i} \; + \; {@co2@}\underline{j} \right) \cdot \left( {@ta1@}\underline{i} {@ta2@}\underline{j} \right) = {@rr[1]@}\cdot{@drr[1]@} + {@rr[2]@}\cdot({@drr[2]@}) = {@ta6@}\).</p>
    </li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>]]></text>
